# ✅ General Interview Tips

- Research the company’s tech stack and mission
- Prepare thoughtful questions for the interviewer
- Practice STAR format (Situation, Task, Action, Result)
- Be honest about your skills — recruiters value clarity
🔹 interview-tips/technical-screening.md
markdown
Copy
Edit
# 🧪 Technical Screening Advice

- Use real-world examples when explaining your work
- Ask clarifying questions before jumping into a coding problem
- Think out loud during live technical interviews
- It's okay to say “I don’t know” — follow up with what you'd do to figure it out
🔹 interview-tips/remote-interviews.md
markdown
Copy
Edit
# 💻 Remote Interview Tips

- Check your setup: camera, mic, lighting, and stable internet
- Have your resume and project links ready to share
- Use headphones to avoid echo
- Look at the camera when speaking
